[A review of trichinellosis in South America including Chile found
that "Most of the outbreaks of human trichinellosis in Mexico,
Argentina and Chile have occurred as a result of the consumption of
undercooked pork or pork products from animals raised under poor
hygienic conditions and which are clandestinely slaughtered"
(Ortega-Pierres MG et al. Epidemiology of trichinellosis in Mexico,
Central and South America. Vet Parasitol. 2000;93:201-25).

HealthMap location: http://healthmap.org/r/01eq - Mod.EP]
